Here is something a little more legit that a friend from higher elo suggested to me and I tried it and it can work really well as a support or really badly. Basically a huge snowbally support that is useless when behind and will only work at low elo.
Sup {{champion:36}} 
{{item:3401}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3065}} {{item:3742}} {{item:2045}} {{item:3111}} 

You are gold efficient, sustain really well, you have really high base damage and can basically throw out suprisingly long range chunking poke and a slow as hard as any mage support basically for free. You are an aggro magnet since if you run at someone they'll probably focus you, you tower dive for days with your ult and you do metric tonnes of damage wherever you go since he's designed to only stack tank items and not bother with damage. Because he stacks only tank items and still does damage he has alot of hp and so his face of the mountain shield is massive. Problems are he lacks any true cc which means that while ahead he provides damage but when behind he's only an aggro magnet and an ineffective one at that, he can be kited which means if he's against a vayne he's going to not be much use and he can't really peel for his adc which means if he can't pull enough aggro from panicking enemies your adc can be bursted down pretty quick. Super fun though and you can feel the terror in the enemy adc when the mundo support runs in and murders them under their own tower and their support can't peel you off. If he gets ahead the mundo support is really hard to stop without the bruiser frontline and positioning of lategame teamfights.

Here is a piece of garbage that can sorta work in low elo
Sup {{champion:30}} 
{{item:3092}} {{item:3027}} {{item:3116}} {{item:3151}} {{item:2045}} {{item:3020}} 

You are basically karthus who only takes cs when the adc backs. You have enough range to bully the enemy adc out of cs without having as huge an issue with mana as regular laning karthus, you probably won't get destroyed by zed or leblanc or fizz, you waveclear really well, you have slows, people probably don't want to dive or all in you and the adc early since if it's clutch you'll probably still break even.

Another build which does kinda ok but feels so weird is triforce garen. It's alot more button mashy than regular garen and is alot easier to play with your high base ad and your general tankiness but he can't really use the mana can he?

